  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nGas price contains 30.5. If you want to change it to 30.1 and tap on delete button to remove \"5\" then gas price becomes \"30\", so comma/dot is deleted automatically. After typing \"1\" you'll get 301. If user is trying to send transaction fast she might not notice the comma/dot absence and use gas price of 301 instead of 30.1\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nonly characters that are explicitly removed by user are removed from the field. There is no auto-correction of the field content. If there is some invalid value then it should not be corrected but error message should be shown, as we do in Amount field. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nif number after comma is deleted then comma/dot is also deleted\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet -> Send transaction -> Advanced -> Transaction Fee\r\n- in Gas price type 30.5\r\n- tap on Delete key to remove 5. Type 1. Check field content\r\n\r\n![comma](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/41373554-f797590e-6f50-11e8-9989-2659e3f1e332.gif)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly build june 13\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n",
